.TH log_init 3 "November 2024" "nanologger 1.0.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
log_init \- Log the initialization of a process or resource.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <nanologger.h>
.br
.BI "void log_init(const char *file, int line, const char *func, const char *fmt, ...);"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B log_init
function logs the initialization of a process or resource.

The function accepts the following parameters:
.TP
.I file
The name of the source file where the initialization occurred.
.TP
.I line
The line number in the source file where the initialization occurred.
.TP
.I func
The name of the function where the initialization occurred.
.TP
.I fmt
A printf-style format string, followed by additional arguments as needed.

.SH RETURN VALUE
This function does not return a value.

.SH NOTES
This function is only available if the
.B DEBUG
macro is set to 3 or higher.

